
Analysis of BLE/Wireshark Log (3-device system)

1. System overview:

The log shows a Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) system involving three devices. The iPhone(Device 1) 
is communicating with multiple BLE peripherals (Device 2 and Device 3) using a shared proprietary
(Encrypted control channel between app ↔ device) protocol. 
However, several frames have flags as:
“out of any connection handle session”
Source and destination BD_ADDR = 00:00:00:00:00:00
This indicates that some frames do not have a valid active BLE connection, so there are corrupted packets



2. Device roles:
   
   Device 1:
	 Name: Viv iphone 17 pro (Apple device)
	 Role: Central controller / initiator
	 Behavior: Sends ATT Write Commands (0x52) to specific handles(e.g. 0xB005), transmits large payloads.
	 orchestrates all sessions and data flow
   
   
   Device 2:
     Name: Amadeus Audio Link
	 Role: Peripheral(gateway device)
	 Behavior: Receives ATT write commands from iPhone
	 
   Device 3:
	 Name: Beo Grace Case
	 Role: Peripheral(accessory device)
	 Behavior: Receives ATT writes + sends notifications to iPhone 
   

3. Primary user scenario

	The primary user scenario is a True Wireless Stereo (TWS) where a smartphone acts as the central controller, 
	connecting to multiple audio/accessory devices to perform setup, initialization, and ongoing control/data 
	exchange.


4. Analysis steps:

	- Identify all devices in the logs by Looking at BD_ADDR and device names
		Found: iPhone, Amadeus Audio Link, Beo Grace Case, Swiss’s Grace

	- Determine the central device
		iPhone appears in most connections, Sends ATT Write Commands (0x52) and Receives notifications from devices

	- Analyze communication pattern
		Write Commands (0x52) + Notifications (0x1B) + Long-lived connections Indicate active session control / data exchange

	- Inspect payload type
		Large payloads (~200–250 bytes) + hex data suggests encrypted application data

	- Look for protocol hints
		ATT + L2CAP used throughout + Custom handles (0xB002, 0xB005)
		Suggests vendor-specific BLE implementation

	- Combine all observations
		One central controller (iPhone) + Multiple connected peripherals + Continuous control/data exchange
		Forms a device ecosystem
